    <section>
        <h1>Introduction</h1>
        
        <h2>1.1 The Cryptocurrency Trading Landscape</h2>
        <p>
            The cryptocurrency market has evolved into a $2+ trillion ecosystem characterized by extreme volatility, 24/7 trading cycles, and unprecedented information flow. Traders face an overwhelming amount of data: price action across hundreds of exchanges, on-chain metrics, social media sentiment, macroeconomic indicators, and technical signals. This information overload, combined with the psychological pressures of high-volatility markets, often leads to emotional decision-making that undermines trading performance.
        </p>

        <h2>1.2 The Emotional Trading Problem</h2>
        <p>
            Research consistently shows that emotional trading—driven by fear, greed, or FOMO (fear of missing out)—is one of the primary causes of retail trader losses. Humans are neurologically wired to make irrational decisions under uncertainty, particularly when financial stakes are high. Common emotional trading patterns include:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Panic selling</strong> during market corrections</li>
            <li><strong>FOMO buying</strong> at local tops</li>
            <li><strong>Confirmation bias</strong> leading to selective information processing</li>
            <li><strong>Loss aversion</strong> causing premature profit-taking or holding losers too long</li>
            <li><strong>Recency bias</strong> overweighting recent events in decision-making</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>1.3 Aigen AI's Approach</h2>
        <p>
            Aigen AI addresses this fundamental challenge by providing rational, data-driven analysis that removes emotional bias from the trading equation. Rather than making trading decisions for users or providing guaranteed signals, Aigen AI serves as an analytical framework that helps traders think clearly, assess risk objectively, and make informed decisions based on statistical probability rather than emotional reaction.
        </p>
    </section>

