        <h2>3.1 Core Philosophy</h2>
        <p>
            Aigen AI is built on three foundational principles:
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>No Guarantees</strong>: We do not promise profits or predict the future. Markets are probabilistic, not deterministic.</li>
            <li><strong>Rational Framework</strong>: We provide objective analysis to help traders make informed decisions based on data, not emotions.</li>
            <li><strong>User Autonomy</strong>: Traders retain full control over their decisions. Aigen AI is a tool for clarity, not an automated trading system.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>3.2 What Aigen AI Does</h2>
        <p>
            Aigen AI processes multiple data streams and presents traders with:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Micro Analysis</strong>: Short-term price action, volume patterns, and immediate market conditions</li>
            <li><strong>Macro Analysis</strong>: Long-term trends, market regimes, and structural context</li>
            <li><strong>Risk Assessment</strong>: Quantified risk metrics, volatility measures, and probability-weighted outcomes</li>
            <li><strong>Sentiment Analysis</strong>: Social media, news, and on-chain sentiment indicators</li>
            <li><strong>On-Chain Intelligence</strong>: Blockchain data analysis for Solana ecosystem</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3.3 What Aigen AI Does NOT Do</h2>
        <p>
            To set proper expectations, Aigen AI explicitly does <strong>not</strong>:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Provide guaranteed trading signals or "calls"</li>
            <li>Execute trades automatically on users' behalf</li>
            <li>Promise specific returns or profitability</li>
            <li>Replace the need for users to think critically about their trades</li>
            <li>Offer financial advice or personalized investment recommendations</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="note">
            <strong>Note:</strong> Aigen AI is a decision-support tool, not a decision-making system. The ultimate responsibility for trading decisions remains with the user.
        </div>
    </section>

