    <section>
        <h1>Micro Analysis Framework</h1>

        <h2>7.1 Definition</h2>
        <p>
            <strong>Micro analysis</strong> focuses on short-term market dynamics, typically spanning minutes to days. This includes:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Intraday price action and volume patterns</li>
            <li>Order book analysis (bid-ask spread, depth)</li>
            <li>Short-term momentum and oscillators</li>
            <li>Immediate market sentiment shifts</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7.2 Key Metrics</h2>

        <h3>Volume Profile Analysis</h3>
        <p>
            Identifies areas of high trading activity to determine support/resistance zones and fair value areas.
        </p>

        <h3>Relative Strength Index (RSI)</h3>
        <p>
            Measures overbought/oversold conditions on multiple timeframes. Divergences between price and RSI signal potential reversals.
        </p>

        <h3>Bollinger Bands & Volatility</h3>
        <p>
            Quantifies current volatility relative to historical norms. Band contractions often precede significant moves.
        </p>

        <h2>7.3 Use Cases</h2>
        <p>
            Micro analysis is particularly valuable for:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Day traders</strong> seeking optimal entry/exit points</li>
            <li><strong>Scalpers</strong> capitalizing on short-term inefficiencies</li>
            <li><strong>Swing traders</strong> timing position entries within broader macro trends</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

