    <section>
        <h1>Macro Analysis Framework</h1>

        <h2>8.1 Definition</h2>
        <p>
            <strong>Macro analysis</strong> examines long-term market structure and context, typically spanning weeks to months. This provides the "big picture" necessary for strategic positioning.
        </p>

        <h2>8.2 Market Regime Detection</h2>
        <p>
            Using clustering algorithms and statistical tests, Aigen AI classifies the current market environment:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Bull Market</strong>: Sustained uptrend with higher highs and higher lows</li>
            <li><strong>Bear Market</strong>: Sustained downtrend with lower highs and lower lows</li>
            <li><strong>Range-Bound</strong>: Sideways consolidation within defined support/resistance</li>
            <li><strong>High Volatility</strong>: Large swings without clear directional bias</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8.3 Cross-Asset Correlation</h2>
        <p>
            Understanding how crypto correlates with traditional markets provides crucial context:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Crypto vs. Equities</strong>: Correlation with S&P 500, NASDAQ</li>
            <li><strong>Crypto vs. Commodities</strong>: Gold, oil, and their macroeconomic drivers</li>
            <li><strong>DXY (US Dollar Index)</strong>: Inverse correlation analysis</li>
            <li><strong>Interest Rates</strong>: Fed policy and risk-on/risk-off dynamics</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8.4 Integration with Micro</h2>
        <p>
            The power of Aigen AI lies in synthesizing micro and macro perspectives:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Alignment</strong>: High-conviction setups when micro and macro agree</li>
            <li><strong>Divergence</strong>: Caution when short-term signals contradict long-term structure</li>
            <li><strong>Context</strong>: Micro opportunities are framed within macro regime</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

