        </p>

        <h3>Drawdown Analysis</h3>
        <p>
            Maximum historical drawdowns and current drawdown from peak provide context for risk tolerance and position sizing.
        </p>

        <h2>9.2 Position Sizing Recommendations</h2>
        <p>
            Based on user-defined risk tolerance and account size, the platform suggests appropriate position sizes using frameworks like:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Fixed Fractional</strong>: Risk a fixed percentage of capital per trade</li>
            <li><strong>Kelly Criterion</strong>: Optimize position size based on edge and odds</li>
            <li><strong>Volatility-Adjusted</strong>: Scale position size inversely with volatility</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

